clustermesh-apiserver completion fish 
 Generate the autocompletion script for fish 
 Synopsis 
 Generate the autocompletion script for the fish shell. 
 To load completions in your current shell session: 
 clustermesh-apiserver completion fish | source
 
 To load completions for every new session, execute once: 
 clustermesh-apiserver completion fish > ~/.config/fish/completions/clustermesh-apiserver.fish
 
 You will need to start a new shell for this setup to take effect. 
 clustermesh-apiserver completion fish [flags]
 
 Options 
   -h, --help              help for fish
      --no-descriptions   disable completion descriptions
 
 SEE ALSO 
 
 clustermesh-apiserver completion 	 - Generate the autocompletion script for the specified shell
